title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 7 data points.
Overall Share of respondents has increased over the Year.

Share of respondents is slightly increasing from Over_55_years to 45-54_years, roughly constant from 45-54_years to 35-44_years, slightly increasing from 35-44_years to 25-34_years, roughly decreasing from 25-34_years to 18-24_years, and lastly roughly constant from 18-24_years to 6-11_years.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 35-44_years and 25-34_years.
Max Share of respondents about 22.0 was recorded at Year 25-34_years
Min Share of respondents about 8.0 was recorded at Year Over_55_years
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of respondents, with a total of 7 data points. The chart has 2 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 25-34_years to 6-11_years.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is slightly increasing which exists from Over_55_years to 25-34_years.
